Olympic High girls&rsquo; football team won their first two preliminary matches to put their Nairobi Region Secondary Schools Sports Association Games title defence on course at Lenana School yesterday.Olympic won both matches in identical 7-0 score-lines against Mt. Larvena and Our Lady of Mercy - Shauri Moyo in Pool &lsquo;A&rsquo;.In the match against Our Lady, Akoth Manyala grabbed a hat trick as Wairimu Mwangi netted a brace. Salome Drialer and Dora Achieng scored one goal each for the reigning national under 16 champions.Maina Wanjigi defeated Nembu Girls 2-1 in Pool &lsquo;B&rsquo; as State House Girls trounced Umoja&rsquo;s Peter Kibukosya 3-0 on Pool &lsquo;D.&rsquo;In the boys category, Dandora thwarted St. Justino 1-0 in a Pool &lsquo;D&rsquo; face off, Eastleigh edged Lenana 2-0, Our Lady of Fatima defeated Olympic High 0-1, as Pool &lsquo;C&rsquo;s Brown Hill won 2-0 against Pumwani.Upper Hill recorded the highest scoring of the day when they clobbered Moi Forces Academy 4-0. John Odira opened the rout barely 15 minutes into the game and Washington Odoyo&rsquo;s goal in the 20th minute gave Upper Hill a 2-0 lead at the break. Finly Osoro and Kevin Oduor netted one goal each in the 45th and 50th minutes respectively.Volleyball holders Hospital Hill Boys started their campaign to retain the regional crown on the right foot as they beat Our Lady of Fatima 3-0 (25-13, 25-14, 25-13) in their Pool &lsquo;A&rsquo; tie.In the girls competition, Soweto beat Mt. Larvena 3-0 (25-3, 25-5, 25-9) and Nembu won 3-0 (25-15, 25-11, 25-17) against St. Hannah.Meanwhile, racket games commence today where lawn tennis is due to serve off at Nairobi Club, while table tennis and badminton will be played at Lenana School.